.TH "sti_vtg_get_pixel_number" 9 "sti_vtg_get_pixel_number" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sti_vtg_get_pixel_number \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" sti_vtg_get_pixel_number
.BI "(struct drm_display_mode mode "  ","
.BI "int x "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mode" 12
display mode to be used
.IP "x" 12
row
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the pixel number according to the display mode taking
into account the Sync and Back Porch information.
Pixels are counted from 0.
